text: Kodiak Island Borough is a borough in the U.S. state of Alaska. As of the 2020 census, the population was 13,101. The borough seat is Kodiak. The borough is located on Kodiak Island and has the same boundaries as the Kodiak Archipelago. == References == Category:Alaska boroughs Category:1960s establishments in Alaska Category:1963 establishments in the United States
title: Kodiak Island Borough, Alaska
